oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Georgette Jones - 2011-05-28
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance and interview by Georgette Jones from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on May 28, 2011. Companion to a Tammy Wynette exhibit.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Georgette Jones;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Performance includes; Your Good Girls Gonna Go Bad; Apartment #9; I Don't Wanna Play House; D.I.V.O.R.C.E.; Golden Ring (with Bill Yates); We're Gonna Hold On (with Bill Yates); Til' I Can Make It On My Own (with Yvonne Abdon); They Call It Making Love (with Yvonne Abdon); Amazing Grace/I'll Fly Away/Will The Circle Be Unbroken/I Saw The Light; You And Me; Womanhood; Near You (with Charlie Allen); Two Story House (with Charlie Allen); Another Chance; I Hope You Knew; Stand By Your Man. Interview conducted by Ali Tonn. Performance of Slightly Used Woman.
